name: Victorian Poetry and Prose
description: Victorian writers (such as Darwin, Tennyson, Browning, Wilde, Nightingale, Christina Rossetti, Kipling) respond to crisis transition: the Industrial Revolution, the Idea of Progress, and the "Woman Question"; conflicting claims of liberty and equality, empire and nation, theology and natural selection; the Romantic Inheritance Art-for-Art's -Sake, Fin de siècle and Decadence. [36L]
prerequisites: 1.0 credit in ENG and 3.0 additional credits
